TrekMate Deployment Guide (AWS EC2)

1. Overview

- Server: AWS EC2, Amazon Linux 2023, t3.micro
- Backend: Node.js (Express) on port 5000
- Frontend: React (Create React App) – static build
- Process Manager: PM2
- Web Server / Reverse Proxy: Nginx
- Database: MongoDB Atlas
- Domain: trekmate.online (+ www.trekmate.online)
- HTTPS: Let’s Encrypt (certbot, nginx plugin)

Repository layout

~/trekmate
  ├── be/          # backend
  ├── fe/          # frontend
  └── deploy.sh    # deployment script


2. EC2 Setup

2.1 Launch instance

- AMI: Amazon Linux 2023 kernel 6.1
- Instance type: t3.micro
- Key pair: create & download (e.g. trekmate-key.pem)
- Security group inbound rules:
  - SSH (22) – ideally restricted to your IP
  - HTTP (80)
  - HTTPS (443)

2.2 SSH access

On your local machine (PowerShell example):

cd C:\path\to\pem
ssh -i "trekmate-key.pem" ec2-user@<PUBLIC_IP>

Type yes the first time to accept the host fingerprint.


3. Base packages

sudo dnf update -y
sudo dnf install -y git nginx


4. Node.js + NVM + PM2

4.1 Install NVM

curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm"
. "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh"
. "$NVM_DIR/bash_completion"

Every new SSH session:
export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm"; . "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh"; . "$NVM_DIR/bash_completion"

4.2 Install Node 20

nvm install 20
nvm use 20

4.3 Install PM2

npm install -g pm2


5. Clone project

cd ~
git clone https://github.com/<USER>/<REPO>.git trekmate
cd trekmate


6. Environment files

6.1 Backend – ~/trekmate/be/.env

MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://<user>:<password>@<cluster>/<dbname>?appName=trekmate
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-in-production
PORT=5000

6.2 Frontend – ~/trekmate/fe/.env

Production (HTTPS):

REACT_APP_API_URL=https://trekmate.online/api
REACT_APP_DEV_MODE=false
REACT_APP_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key_here

Local development (optional):

REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api


7. Backend with PM2

cd ~/trekmate/be

if [ -f package-lock.json ]; then
  npm ci --omit=dev
else
  npm install --omit=dev
fi

pm2 start src/index.js --name trekmate-api
pm2 save

pm2 startup systemd
# run the command printed by pm2 as sudo
pm2 save

Check:

pm2 status


8. Nginx configuration

Edit file:

sudo nano /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf

Content:

server {
    listen 80;
    listen [::]:80;
    server_name trekmate.online www.trekmate.online;

    root /usr/share/nginx/html;
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri /index.html;
    }

    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000/;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header   Host              $host;
        proxy_set_header   X-Real-IP         $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header   X-Forwarded-For   $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header   X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}

Apply:

sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl enable nginx
sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo systemctl reload nginx


9. Frontend build & static deploy

cd ~/trekmate/fe

if [ -f package-lock.json ]; then
  npm ci
else
  npm install
fi

npm run build

sudo rm -rf /usr/share/nginx/html/*
sudo cp -r build/* /usr/share/nginx/html/

sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx

Test with http://<PUBLIC_IP>.


10. Domain configuration

At DNS provider for trekmate.online:

- A record: @ → <PUBLIC_IP>
- CNAME record: www → trekmate.online

After propagation, http://trekmate.online should open the site.


11. HTTPS with Let’s Encrypt

Install:

sudo dnf install -y certbot python3-certbot-nginx

Issue cert:

sudo certbot --nginx -d trekmate.online -d www.trekmate.online

- Choose redirect all HTTP to HTTPS.

Test auto-renew:

sudo certbot renew --dry-run

Now use https://trekmate.online.


12. One-command deployment script

Create ~/trekmate/deploy.sh:

#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -e

echo "=========== TrekMate deploy ==========="


echo ""
echo "=== [BE] Install dependencies ==="
cd ~/trekmate/be
if [ -f package-lock.json ]; then
  npm ci --omit=dev || npm install --omit=dev
else
  npm install --omit=dev
fi


echo ""
echo "=== [BE] Start/Restart PM2 ==="
if pm2 describe trekmate-api >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  pm2 restart trekmate-api
else
  pm2 start src/index.js --name trekmate-api
fi


echo ""
echo "=== [FE] Install dependencies ==="
cd ~/trekmate/fe
if [ -f package-lock.json ]; then
  npm ci || npm install
else
  npm install
fi


echo ""
echo "=== [FE] Build production ==="
npm run build


echo ""
echo "=== [FE] Copy build -> /usr/share/nginx/html ==="
sudo rm -rf /usr/share/nginx/html/*
sudo cp -r build/* /usr/share/nginx/html/


echo ""
echo "=== [Nginx] Test & reload ==="
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx


echo ""
echo "✅ Deploy completed successfully!"

Make executable:

cd ~/trekmate
chmod +x deploy.sh

Deployment flow

Local:

git add .
git commit -m "Update"
git push origin main

On EC2:

ssh -i "trekmate-key.pem" ec2-user@<PUBLIC_IP>
cd ~/trekmate
git pull origin main
./deploy.sh


13. Google Analytics (GA4)

1. Create GA4 property for trekmate.online.
2. Get Measurement ID: G-XXXXXXXXXX.
3. On local machine edit fe/public/index.html and add inside <head>:

<!-- Google tag (gtag.js) -->
<script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-XXXXXXXXXX"></script>
<script>
  window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
  function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
  gtag('js', new Date());
  gtag('config', 'G-XXXXXXXXXX');
</script>

4. Commit & push; then on EC2:

cd ~/trekmate
git pull origin main
./deploy.sh

5. Open https://trekmate.online and check Realtime in GA dashboard.


14. Common issues & fixes

14.1 Mixed content (blocked:mixed-content)

- Page is HTTPS but API URL is HTTP.
- Ensure FE .env in production:

  REACT_APP_API_URL=https://trekmate.online/api

- Rebuild FE and redeploy (./deploy.sh).

14.2 JSON parse error with <!DOCTYPE ...>

- FE is calling a URL that returns HTML (like Nginx default page) instead of JSON.
- Check:
  - REACT_APP_API_URL
  - Nginx /api/ proxy block

14.3 deploy.sh: No such file or directory

- Ensure you are in correct folder:

  cd ~/trekmate
  ls

- If missing, recreate deploy.sh with the script above and:

  chmod +x deploy.sh

14.4 Nginx 403 / 404 after deploy

- Check that build files exist:

  ls /usr/share/nginx/html

- Ensure Nginx root matches:

  root /usr/share/nginx/html;
  index index.html;

- Reload Nginx:

  sudo nginx -t
  sudo systemctl reload nginx
